  "title": "Site Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Plan, supervise, and manage daily site operations for infrastructure projects.</li>\n  <li>Review construction drawings, specifications, contracts, and ensure compliance with project requirements.</li>\n  <li>Develop and monitor work schedules, progress, and resource allocation to ensure timely project delivery.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate and liaise with consultants, subcontractors, suppliers, authorities, and internal stakeholders.</li>\n  <li>Ensure site work complies with safety, health, environmental, and regulatory requirements.</li>\n  <li>Control and monitor project costs, manpower, and materials to achieve efficiency.</li>\n  <li>Conduct regular site inspections and resolve technical or operational issues.</li>\n  <li>Lead site meetings, prepare progress reports, and update management on project status.</li>\n  <li>Handle claims, variations, and ensure proper documentation.</li>\n  <li>Perform any other duties as assigned by the Project Manager or senior management.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s Degree in Civil Engineering, Construction Management, or related field.</li>\n  <li>At least <strong>5 years’ experience</strong> in civil/infrastructure projects.</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of construction methodologies, contracts, and regulations in Singapore.</li>\n  <li>Proven ability to lead site teams, manage subcontractors, and deliver projects successfully.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in MS Office and project management software.</li>\n  <li>Strong problem-solving skills, leadership, and communication abilities.</li>\n  <li>Working Location: East</li>\n</ul>",
